<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920113-0049</DOCNO><DOCID>920113-0049.</DOCID><HL>   Technology Brief -- Integrated Device Technology Inc.:   Third-Period Loss Expected;   Layoffs Are Set, Pay Is Cut</HL><DATE>01/13/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   IDTI LABOR</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SEMICONDUCTORS, INTEGRATED CHIPS (SEM)</IN><NS>EARNINGS PROJECTIONS (ERP)LABOR, UNIONS, STRIKES, WAGES, RECRUITMENT (LAB)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Integrated Device Technology Inc., Santa Clara, Calif.,said it expects to report a third-quarter loss of $1.6million to $2.6 million, or six cents to 10 cents a share.The company imposed layoffs and pay cuts to reduce its costs.   The maker of integrated circuits said it cut 100employees, or 5% of its 2,000 employee work force, andslashed salaries 10% for company executives, and 4% forcertain other employees; remaining salaries were frozen.</LP><TEXT>   The anticipated loss for the quarter ended Dec. 29compares with profit of $256,000, or one cent a share, onrevenue of $48.2 million a year earlier. Revenue for theperiod should grow 5% to more than $50 million. The companysaid that although new orders were strong, it wasn't able toship enough product during the quarter to offset the highcosts of adding new manufacturing capacity.   The cuts are expected to have a &quot;positive impact&quot; onfuture quarters, the company said.   In over-the-counter trading Friday, Integrated closed at$6.375, up 12.5 cents.</TEXT></DOC>